{
  "doc_id": "7342",
  "text": "To detect bulk small RNAs in gels, total RNA was extracted from equal numbers of mating wild-type and TWI11 MAC+MIC-KO cells at 3 hpm. RNA was separated in 15% acrylamide-urea gels and stained with GelRed (GENTAUR) [CITATION_1] . High-throughput sequencing of small RNAs was performed as described [12, [CITATION_2] . The raw data used for the analysis shown in Figure 3 were obtained in a previous study and can be found in the NCBI Gene Expression Omnibus under accession number GSE38768. The other sequencing data were obtained in this study and are deposited under accession number GSE111525.",
